The forces of the mega strike are coming together
The trade unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will form their strike commission on Friday, which will be responsible for coordinating Monday's indefinite strike.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health insurance, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic jams as rail traffic will be almost completely stopped and employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 1 p.m.
The League Unions will announce on Friday afternoon the details of their Monday strike, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be formed, it will serve as the coordinator of Monday's actions.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and, starting Monday, organizations joining the strike will stop work indefinitely if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health insurance, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not pass the Health Insurance Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strike action.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide what to do next.
According to the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the law on health insurance will take place only late in the evening or even at night.
Due to the strike planned for Monday, major traffic jams are planned: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Vol<0xC3><0xA1>n companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will be blocked as well.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call for strikes, the list of which is constantly updated on the League's website.
Some organizations report going on strike for an indefinite period of time, others have declared a temporary stoppage of work.
Until Thursday afternoon the M<0xC3><0x81>V (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Railways Union (VDSZSZ) have failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, but as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more are taking the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the start of service until 1 p.m., Budapest Airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Union of Teachers and the Union of Democratic Teachers will strike for two hours.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country alternately, the Health and Social Sector Employees' Union (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will strike a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, requires the government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new conception to the social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be put in place from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim seeks a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, that would allow the functions that deserve it to pass into the system before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Union Libre des Cheminots (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railways and the expectation of another proposal.
