Did you miss an appointment?
At best he is sorry and tries to arrange things by calling the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, the matter is settled with an apology.
Before having painful explanations, it is helpful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that doesn’t belong to you?
There’s nothing more annoying than wanting to take a file, an office tool, or the phone and you can’t find them anywhere.
Do you remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Don't take anything from your colleagues without asking or they're right to be angry at you for stinging their good.
Do not bring envelopes, post-it in your pocket because it can be annoying that there are no more and that you need it right away.
Are you talking about the privacy of your colleagues?
There are no good ways to stop potions from spreading.
Who did what, with whom?
Or and why?
Don’t tell everyone your information (suppositions) about the privacy of your colleagues!
If a colleague shares their intimate secrets with you, don’t abuse their trust!
Bury the shared information in you and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware of it.
Are you declaring yourself sick for no good reason?
When you call the office and you declare yourself sick under the pretext of a tearing headache because you feel bad or you feel you need rest that day, think about the fact that your work, your urgent affairs, your future missions must be carried out by someone else in your place.
Don't bother your colleagues!
If you know in advance that the next day you are not going to work or that something can happen that would force you to stay at home, do not forget to warn your boss and colleagues to prevent them from being surprised by your absence the next day.
Chilling, tingling, phone
You get into your job, but your co-workers' squeezing pulls you out of it?
Did you become, unintentionally, witness a conversation over the phone that you would have done better not to listen to?
Don’t bother your colleagues with shouting, chanting, talking out loud (which you’re leading over their heads), kicking, big words, or loud voiced discontent.
They can bother even if your colleagues are not immersed in a project (writing, design, organization).
Are you blaming others for a mistake?
If your work is not done for the set deadline, you forget to send an important mail or message, do not blame anyone for this forgetfulness!
Do not put it on the account of the possible chaos in the office or your noisy colleagues!
Recognize it if you have made a mistake and if it has presented disadvantages for others, correct the mistake!
Ask how you could make up for your mistake, make up for the neglect!
Do you feel at home in the office?
Putting a jogging and slippers is comfortable at home but they are not suitable at the office!
Do not put comfortable jogging even if your function allows it!
Do not be neglected, respect your colleagues and yourself by dressing properly, and if your job requires it by putting on nice and elegant clothes, to go to work!
