What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible damages, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And that is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the odds.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower casualty rate due to their prudence.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tended to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of drawbacks when signing an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as the low experience in driving and seniority of the driver's license.
While the ideal way to be well insured is to take out insurance at any risk, there are other, more economical options.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for free-of-charge all-risk insurance, so that they get the coverage of all-risk insurance at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," said Luis Noguera, First Europa's head of online insurance in Spain.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid damages as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a sanction is an increase in the basic tariff.
“Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” Noguera explains.
Beyond the age of 25, this becomes easier for drivers when signing a contract with insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose any risk insurance with franchise.
“Normally young people cannot enjoy the experience previously gained after an accident,” says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better that he negotiates insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance at any risk with deductibles (can be 300 euros), or third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have more casual driving and they have more purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” Noguera said.
For retirees, any risk insurance with deductibles is preferable (being 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us the most according to our personal situation.
