Some films have yet to mature - those that are worth classic works on Vietnam today "The Deer Hunter", "Apocalypse Now" or "Full Metal Jackett" have by no means been unanimously celebrated in their time as masterpieces.
But perhaps today we also know just too much about the conflicts of the world, where each hecatomb arrives live on two screens at the same time at home,
And this delighted the writers the lack of scruples they need to tell beautiful stories.
“To be or not to be” or “The Dictator” actually became just as good also because Lubtisch and Chaplin didn’t yet know how much the Nazi regime really dominated.
